PROMOTING THE PLATFORM 5Ô∏è‚É£ ‚úÖ In June we have created new marketing activities, dedicated to the launch of Predictions module, with world-known sports stars. üèí NHL star Nikita Kucherov held an AMA session for TokenStars community. üëâ Read more on Medium (https://medium.com/@TokenStars/money-or-game-nikita-kucherov-makes-the-right-choice-6df76d2926a9) or on Instagram (https://www.instagram.com/p/Bk2pgKaAlIQ/)‚öΩÔ∏è World Cup champion Gianluca Zambrotta supported the launch of TokenStars Predictions Contest on Instagram (https://www.instagram.com/p/Bkr1qRDnPA3/)  INFORMING CRYPTO AUDIENCE ABOUT TOKENS 6Ô∏è‚É£ ‚úÖ To promote TokenStars project we have released new banner advertising. Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: We think that after new modules are launched and new players are signed the demand for our tokens will increase.  TokenStars has already launched 2 modules: 1. Auction module which already held charity auctions from world-known celebrities. Check it out here: https://tokenstars.com/charity  2. Voting module which already had first 3 decentralized polls. http://voting.tokenstars.com  3. In May 2018 we plan to launch Sports predictions module.  Check out this article and video to better understand the short-term strategy explained by our CEO https://medium.com/@TokenStars/ama-session-with-tokenstars-ceo-pavel-stukolov-db83b918393d  Let me explain you the economy of our tokens.  ACE and TEAM tokens are the utility tokens which offer unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc. These services are bought for tokens. The more often a token is used, the better it is for all participants.  Agency commissions will be paid in tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow. As a result, the agency commissions will grow. Commission will be converted into tokens, by buying tokens on the market.  So the more revenue the project has, the more tokens will be bought. This should positively impact the internal economy. However, bear in mind that markets are unpredictable.

Author: TokenStars

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: ‚≠êÔ∏è Update on the exchanges for TEAM token: ‚≠êÔ∏è   1Ô∏è‚É£ We've confirmed with Qryptos that token holders from Japan are not allowed to register at the exchange. This does not create equal opportunities for the token holders and is a 'stopper' for initial listing.   2Ô∏è‚É£ We've heard the communities' (loud) opinion that daily trading volume at Qryptos is too low. It will be significantly larger in June after the planned merger with Quoine exchange. But not for now. We've heard you.   3Ô∏è‚É£ Based on that, we've decided: a). Qryptos is still a good option for listing in future after merger, b). We should look for other exchanges with larger volumes, c). If we still decide to list on Qryptos, than it shouldn't be the only exchange, and the listing on 2 exchanges shall happen on the same day.  4Ô∏è‚É£ At the moment, we're waiting for the final offers from 2 larger exchanges. After we get this information we'll update you on the next steps. 1-2 weeks is the estimated time frame. Please stay patient.  P.S. We'd like to remind that at the time of ACE listing on OKEx it was only approaching top-10 by daily trading volume and the community initially didn't like that exchange either. We believe that the situation with Qryptos is very similar, this exchange will grow a lot after merger. So we shall not rule this option out completely.

Body: ‚≠êÔ∏è Did you ask your question to an Italian football star and our Ambassador Gianluca Zambrotta in AMA session by TokenStars? ‚≠êÔ∏è  ‚öΩÔ∏è Check out if he picked yours! Here are some answers for the third celebrity AMA session by TokenStars:  ‚ùì Which team would be the next World Champion? It‚Äôs not easy to choose because it is a very tough tournament. Russia that will host the World Cup could have an advantage so it can be a protagonist. Then Portugal who won the last European Championship, Brazil, France, Spain. All of them can win the trophy.  ‚ùì Who would you be if you did not become a football player? It‚Äôs not easy to answer to this question but after school I had already found a job in a textile firm. My hometown Como is the city of silk, so probably I would have worked in the textile industry.  ‚ùì What is your life goal for the next 10 years? My main life goal for the next 10 years is to still have happiness and health for my family. My wife, my son Riccardo, for all of us. Regarding my professional goal I‚Äôm focused on my work here in China with Jiangsu Suning FC, it‚Äôs a very important experience and I want to do my best. In the future my goal is to continue my career as a coach.  ‚ùì What is his vision about TokenStars? TokenStars is a very interesting project because it assists and supports young athletes. Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: ¬´We have around 60 people in the IMG Tennis team, and they all have connections. I know everyone in the  Japanese Tennis Federation who knew about [Nishikori]¬ª. This Rolodex relationship building approach has certain  advantages for scouting. But: ‚Ä¢ it is expensive (60 full-time salaried employees amount to roughly $4 million in costs per year, excluding travel),  IMG is a monster, and smaller agencies can‚Äôt a ord so many employees ‚Ä¢ it is di icult to scale (agents neglect traditionally non-tennis countries like India or Brazil) ‚Ä¢ it is subjective (based on the gut feeling of an expert, who never managed to become a pro player himself) ‚Ä¢ it is open to corruption (including so called ‚Äòkick-backs‚Äô when part of the contract amount is paid back to the  scout in exchange for his favorable review of the candidate)  Old-fashioned scouting process should be replaced with a decentralized  approach. We believe that the Global Scouting Network of 600 part-time  analysts spread globally and properly motivated  financially will be more  efficient than the full-time 60 employees focused on making friends with local  Tennis Federations‚Äô presidents.  You can read about Scouting more in the White Paper.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: You know, ~20% of both top 300 in rankings (ATP and WTA) are overlooked by traditional agencies, so we can offer them our Network‚Äôs advertising capacities and expertise.  Even elite players are open to changing agents and TokenStars will consider this possibility after initial launch.  Old-fashioned scouting process should be replaced with a decentralized  approach. We believe that the Global Scouting Network of 600 part-time  analysts spread globally and properly motivated  financially will be more  efficient than the full-time 60 employees focused on making friends with local  Tennis Federations‚Äô presidents.

TokenStars, the first celebrity management platform on blockchain, today announces that Nomadic Capital has participated in the TEAM token sale and will help the company to expand its activities in the MENA region through various channels to ensure both awareness and growth. About TokenStars  TokenStars is a blockchain-based platform which connects rising talents and successful professionals in sports and entertainment with fans and advertisers. ACE and TEAM tokens by TokenStars provide the fans opportunities to interact with their favorite athletes and celebrities as well as to support their careers. Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars will provide fans with a wide range of options to bring interaction with their favorite celebrities at the new level. Fans will receive opportunity to redeem TEAM tokens either for exclusive offers and connections or for  general online communications with stars.  Exclusive offers from stars. Token holders may spend tokens on exclusive offers and real-life events such as live meetings, trainings, match tickets, concerts, etc. Announcement and bookings will be implemented by the platform. Admission prices will be either fixed or auction-based and will be paid only in TEAM tokens.  Online communication. Specialized platform tools for online communications will be developed. - One-way video casts of selected exclusive events will be available to the token holders. Access to the content will be granted automatically after the platform calls Ethereum through the API and verifies the user logging into the cast owns required number of tokens that are not charged from his or her account but only are used for verification purposes. - Two-way video and text chats. Paying customers will be able to join two-way communication with the star. Due to apparent reasons, the number of fans the star will be able to communicate with at the same time is limited. Pricing model can be flat or auction-based. Admission fee must be paid in TEAM tokens. - Verified token holders will be able to join the chat in the view-only (read-only) mode free of charge (with advertising monetization).

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Token implementation has the following reason: the endorsements and promotional services will be paid in tokens (fully or in a part of TokenStars commission), so the higher the amount of advertising campaigns ‚Äì the more tokens will be demanded in the market.  Our choice of blockchain as underlying technology of the TokenStars platform allows us to build transparent, scalable and verifiable system for all platform participants, especially for fans, scouts, promoters and advertisers. We will grant fans community leaders with tools to audit the records of blockchain distributed ledger to prove the transparency of interaction and avoid the potential conflicts between the participants.  Our platform will interact with tens of thousands of people (with millions in the future). We aspire to introduce more than 4 billion sports fans to the blockchain world. For the reference, - Top-20 football players have 1.4 billion followers across most popular social media platforms. - The estimated number of FC Manchester United followers is 659 million of people8. This possibly is the largest fan base for a football club in the world.  Furthermore, we plan to work with the celebrities not only in sports, but also in entertainment (movies, music) and expect to have a huge user base.  Every event such as recording of a vote in the poll, collecting report from the promoter, receiving auction bids or registering advertising click will generate blockchain writing down operations. Our in-house advertising will be using blockchain to record all important events for further analysis. Daily number of these events can reach millions.  Using Ethereum blockchain for recording of such big number of events would be impractical mainly because of slow transaction speed and transaction-related expenses.

What can TokenStars provide celebrities with? - bring new endorsement contracts (additional revenue, on top of their existing revenue) - sign non-exclusive promotion agreements - increase the level of the star-fans communication, e.g. online and real-life interaction - enhance the audience involvement - strengthen the brand and increase the advertising value

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: We consider developing the TS platform based on two interacting blockchains: 1. Ethereum for the token-related operations and 2. Private blockchain for the internal platform operations.  TokenStars private blockchain will be built as a network of nodes, maintained by the Company in the early stage of the platform development. Later we plan to delegate the rights (partially or fully) of the nodes‚Äô maintenance to the leaders of the fan community who will be invited to become the part of the network. This will allow us to create a truly distributed network uncontrolled by any single party in the true spirit of blockchain.  We also plan to take advantage of the distributed blockchain technology for fast and efficient scaling of the platform. Network node operators will be able to audit blockchain operations to judge possible conflicts.  TokenStars will produce easy-to install packages of the software required to run a network node and will provide all necessary instructions and worldwide 24/7 support. Network node operators will be compensated for their efforts with the TEAM tokens.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: On the contrary, Many Athletes Are Disappointed by the Current State of Affairs.  IMG is practically a monopoly in tennis. They can dictate terms (from the tournaments a player participates in to the organization of his or her training schedule). They turn down players from smaller countries (as the domestic market is small and there are few opportunities for advertising). And, they make mistakes in their selection process.  Roger Federer left IMG and started his own agency, Team818. He has signed several top-10 players, including Bulgarian star Grigor Dimitrov and Argentine star Juan Martin Del Potro.  Andy Murray left Lagardere and set up a management agency ‚Äú77‚Äù (name of which is inspired by the 77-year wait for a British men‚Äôs singles champion at Wimbledon, that Andy brought to an end in 2013).  As a reason for creating his own agency Murray stated that ‚Äúit will allow him more freedom in decision-making and the chance to become more involved in his business affairs‚Äù.  One of the most remarkable conflicts between an agency and a player was Ivan Lendl‚Äôs case, the winner of seven Grand Slam tournaments and undisputable No.1 in the ATP ranking. Ivan was dissatisfied with the work of agency, cause at the top of his career he experienced lack of attention from his agents. Later Lendl accused Proserv of exploiting his image for ‚Äòpackaging‚Äô with other players at less favorable terms.  Later Lendl left Proserv and started his own agency20.  ACE will collaborate with established pro players: ~20% of both top 300 in rankings (ATP and WTA) are overlooked by traditional agencies, so we can offer them our Network‚Äôs advertising capacities and expertise. Even elite players are open to changing agents and ACE will consider this possibility after initial launch.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: The platform will allow to run custom advertising campaigns such as full-screen video takeovers or full-page branded design or content will be implemented by an in-house developed AdTech solution that will include the following components:  - Wizard that will allow advertisers to specify campaign parameters and upload all creative formats. - Smart-contract based advertising engine that will assure transparent measurement of advertising performance by logging important events into blockchain. - Custom analytical tools that will give insights into campaign results enriched by our audience knowledge. - API to industry-standard analytical suite such as Google Analytics that will allow advertisers to integrate results from TokenStars campaigns into the common reporting practice. - Platform tokens will be used as a universal method of payment for custom advertising. - Data Management Platform (DMP) is the system that purpose is to collect and analyze information about project audience and to use the data for advertising campaigns targeting. As majority of the project visitors will be the authorized users we will be having unique and precise insight of the audience properties, that we will further enrich by integrating with one of the data management platforms. - We will use one of the third-party ad servers or SSPs to run display advertising campaigns on our web properties and apps. Audience segments collected with the DMP will be available for campaign targeting exclusively for the advertisers of TokenStars. - We will be able to run programmatic advertising campaigns on behalf of our clients using exclusive audience data and one of the industry-standard media buying solutions (DSP).[/li][/list]   Case study: ‚ÄòCoca-Cola‚Äô wants to place an ad in ‚ÄòSnowboarders‚Äô Instagram and pay $50 for every submitted application. In a few clicks they develop a contract and make a deal.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: First, ACE is a product token which offers unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc. These services are bought for tokens. The more often a token is used, the better it is for all participants.  Second, agency commissions will be converted into tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow. As a result, the agency commissions will grow. We get our commissions in tokens, which means tokens are to be bought on the market. The more revenue, the more of them are bought. This positively impacts the internal economy.     Third, the ACE token plays a crucial role in the ACE ecosystem, since it provides voting rights in the decentralized community voting mechanism. ACE holders will have the opportunity to vote on various decisions, thus influencing the success of the platform. Then, it serves as a fundamental unit of accounting and a method of payment for its agents, specifically scouts, promoters, and advertisers.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars private blockchain will be built as a network of nodes, maintained by the Company in the early stage of the platform development. Later we plan to delegate the rights (partially or fully) of the nodes‚Äô maintenance to the leaders of the fan community who will be invited to become the part of the network. This will allow us to create a truly distributed network uncontrolled by any single party in the true spirit of blockchain.  We also plan to take advantage of the distributed blockchain technology for fast and efficient scaling of the platform. Network node operators will be able to audit blockchain operations to judge possible conflicts.  TokenStars will produce easy-to install packages of the software required to run a network node and will provide all necessary instructions and worldwide 24/7 support. Network node operators will be compensated for their efforts with the TEAM tokens.

All interactions require TEAM tokens: the higher involvement means higher demand for tokens.

Roland Garros champion. - Robin S√∂derling, a Swedish tennis star, No. 4 in ATP. - Cedric Pioline, No. 5 in ATP ranking. Has shown a strong presence in the media and received multiple endorsements.  6. Launched the platform development. The 1 of the 12 modules is expected to be launched in Q4 2017, as planned.  More information on ACE achievements is available in our blog posts: - On the 15 achievements (Aug, 25) ‚Äì https://medium.com/@TokenStars/15-good-newsfrom-tokenstars-c1cbe7832864 - On the results of the token sale (Oct, 30) ‚Äì https://medium.com/@TokenStars/httpsmedium-com-tokenstars-join-the-team-10-news-from-tokenstars-98464eb711ed

We have chosen blockchain as underlying technology of the platform to allow us to build transparent and verifiable system for all platform  participants, especially for fans, advertisers, talent scouts, as well as regular token holders. TokenStars platform will record in blockchain ledger the events of interaction between the participants, such as voting results, applications from the scouts, auction bids or advertising clicks. All transactions will be kept in blockchain memory pool.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: We did not refuse to use ACE tokens. We use ACE to tokenize tennis sportsmen. ACE vertical is already working: - TokenStars signed the first contract with a PRO tennis player - Veronika Kudermetova, winner of 21 international tournaments (No. 58 in WTA ranking in doubles)  - TokenStars launched the marketing project with Ekaterina Makarova (Olympic Gold medalist in Rio-2016; the winner of Wimbledon, US Open and Roland Garros; No. 33 in WTA singles / No. 3 in doubles) and Veronika Kudermetova;  - TokenStars established partnerships with major media platforms (for tennis we have signed a partnership deal with major sports media such as Tribuna.digital and Sports.ru with 12.5 million MAU);  TEAM token relates to football, hockey, poker, eSports, entertainment and etc. TokeStars is assembling a top-notch sports & entertainment advisory board that will share its expertise to stimulate project growth and help us select the most promising talents and attract large audience of users to TokenStars platform: Lothar Matth√§us (football), Nikita Kucherov (hockey), Alexander Anter (poker), Rico Torres (Hollywood), and others.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TEAM and ACE are tokens Over the course of August, September and October in 2017 we‚Äôve personally met or had phone calls with several Olympic champions, world champions, coaches and agents. On multiple occasions we‚Äôve heard the question ‚ÄòWhy do you separate different kinds of sport into different verticals and use different tokens?‚Äô  Basically, both approaches are viable and have their pros and cons. Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hello! TokenStars is the platform for tokenization of celebrities. TokenStars is long term project. This was not designed as a "hype"-style ICO. But as a classic long marketing driven process.  Let me tell you how TEAM economy works: TokenStars is the first celebrity management platform on blockchain. TEAM by TokenStars connects rising talents and successful PROs in sports and entertainment with fans and advertisers.  Agency commissions will be paid in tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow.  As a result, the agency commissions will grow. Accordingly, sponsors will convert our commissions into tokens, which means buying tokens on the market.  The more revenue, the more will be bought from the market. This positively impacts the internal economy.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars platform is designed as a toolkit, allowing to combine different modules to enable and encourage the interaction between the celebrities, fans (as well as regular token holders), advertisers, professional talent scouts and promoters. It has 12 modules for the community. The first platform Contests & Charity Module is already launched.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Our platform consists of 12 integrated modules that allow participants to connect in a new way. Designed as a toolkit, the platform allows to combine different modules to achieve the required features and capabilities.  Based on their functionality, the modules are part of 4 different layers:  1. Crowdfunding layer, enabling promising talents and celebrities to raise funds.  2. Infrastructure layer, providing functional tools (like voting and scouting) for key platform activities.  3. Fans Community layer, allowing the celebrities to grow their social capital by expanding their loyal fan bases and offering the fans the desired involvement by communicating and participating activities with their favorite stars.  4. Advertising layer, delivering smart & transparent data and engaged audience to brands for more efficient advertising campaigns (by enabling advertising smart contracts and exclusive merchandise sales).

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: ACE agency adheres to the standard commission rate of 20% of the players‚Äô net prize money (excluding local  taxes) and 20-25% sponsorships‚Äô revenue (in case the sponsor is brought by a promoter the latter receives 10%  commission of the  rst contract and 2% of all the following deals).  Before ACE agency‚Äôs initial funding is paid back it has a priority right for revenue proceeds (up to 75% of the prize  money and sponsorship revenue). If a contract expires or is terminated for whatever reason (by ACE agency, by player) then the agency still has  accumulated receivables and the player is expected to pay his debt (except the cases when the player decides to  retire from sports for medical reasons).  It is obligatory for sponsors and players to pay the ACE agency fees and commissions in tokens, so the  sponsors and players will have to buy tokens in the market. The higher the ACE agency revenue ‚Äì the more tokens  are supposed to be bought in the market.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: The platform will allow to run custom advertising campaigns such as full-screen video takeovers or full-page branded design or content will be implemented by an in-house developed AdTech solution that will include the following components:  - Wizard that will allow advertisers to specify campaign parameters and upload all creative formats. - Smart-contract based advertising engine that will assure transparent measurement of advertising performance by logging important events into blockchain. - Custom analytical tools that will give insights into campaign results enriched by our audience knowledge. - API to industry-standard analytical suite such as Google Analytics that will allow advertisers to integrate results from TokenStars campaigns into the common reporting practice. - Platform tokens will be used as a universal method of payment for custom advertising. - Data Management Platform (DMP) is the system that purpose is to collect and analyze information about project audience and to use the data for advertising campaigns targeting. As majority of the project visitors will be the authorized users we will be having unique and precise insight of the audience properties, that we will further enrich by integrating with one of the data management platforms. - We will use one of the third-party ad servers or SSPs to run display advertising campaigns on our web properties and apps. Audience segments collected with the DMP will be available for campaign targeting exclusively for the advertisers of TokenStars. - We will be able to run programmatic advertising campaigns on behalf of our clients using exclusive audience data and one of the industry-standard media buying solutions (DSP).

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: First Players‚Äô Cohort Expected Composition  The rough estimate is to sign:  ‚Ä¢ 2 to 3 in the 13-14 age group, 1 to 3 at the ages of 15-16 (when their existing 2-year contracts expire and many players and parents are disappointed by agencies) ‚Ä¢ 50% boys, 50% girls (although the prize money in men‚Äôs tournaments is higher, women tennis players are more often chosen by brands as models for commercials) ‚Ä¢ From 1/3 and up to 1/2 of the cohort from outside traditional tennis countries  We will specifically target traditionally non-tennis countries with large domestic market (Japan, China, India, Brazil etc.) because even with relatively modest results such a player will be considered a star for life in his home country, like Guga Kuerten from Brazil.  The domestic country market size is an important criterion. ‚ÄúIf there is a young talent from Croatia, he had better be good, because if he‚Äôs number 50 in the world we are not going to be able to do our job. But If he is from Japan, or India or China, he can be number 50 in the world; this is a totally different story".

Body: Hi, TokenStars helps to scouts with the following:  ‚Ä¢ Crunch data (local kids‚Äô and juniors‚Äô rankings, and local tournament results) and determine potential ‚Äòtargets‚Äô ‚Ä¢ Reach out to players, parents, coaches, and tennis club owners in local social networks ‚Ä¢ Submit applications via the ACE website to our full-time scouts ‚Ä¢ Hold assessment sessions at players‚Äô locations (no need for expensive 2-week travel to a global HQ, like IMG does) ‚Ä¢ Use the most modern connected equipment during assessments, for example, the Babolat smart racquet which gathers a variety of data during the game (serve speed, shots hit map, rally time, etc.) ‚Ä¢ Use a unique internal players‚Äô assessment checklist (50+ parameters ranging from the strictly technical side to the players‚Äô psychotype or their parents‚Äô involvement). This will allow for development of a standardized process and legitimate player comparisons

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hello! Let us explain you the core idea. Brands seek new channels of promotion with highly engaged audience and demand transparent and adjustable tools to run advertising campaigns.  We understand that in order to encourage collaboration between huge number of participants TokenStars shall develop scalable digital solutions and competitive incentives for all parties.  Therefore, we build the modular blockchain platform that will allow participants to combine its blocks and achieve the desired results. Eventually it will change the way how celebrities connect with their fans and advertisers, making it more efficient and valuable.  We introduce TEAM token to empower the interaction between parties. TEAM tokens (ERC-20 standard) will serve as a form of access to the TokenStars platform and as an internal currency, required for the majority of operations and transactions within our ecosystem.  Have you seen our Brands and Advertising Layer of the TokenStars platform?  3 modules, providing smart solutions & transparent data to brands for running more efficient advertising campaigns with highly engaged audience.  Read the details here in our White Paper (from the page 28): https://tokenstars.com/upload/files/team_whitepaper.pdf

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars and brands will be selling different stars-related items through a web store. The items can be purchased with TEAM tokens for fixed price or at an auction. E-Commerce module of the platform is planned to be implemented with a third-party solution that allows payments with Ethereum-based cryptocurrencies and tokens. Shopify is one of the platforms we consider. We are aware that other crypto-oriented e-commerce suites are in development now. We will choose the best performing e-commerce suite at a later platform development phase. Case study: tennis star ‚ÄòMaria‚Äô has a contract with Nike, she sets up an online store with autographed Nike products via TokenStars e-commerce module.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Talents pass the automatic screening (based on their youth stats and results) and offline assessment, conducted by TokenStars licensed scouts, that provides information for the future selection of candidates for voting and contract proposal. Any token holder can register as an Analyst and gain access to the talent‚Äôs data and to the voting. Measures will be taken to protect personal-sensitive information of the talent and the scout. Analysts can give their votes for or against signing of the contract with the new star candidate. Number of votes equals to the number of TEAM tokens held by every analyst. The voting is conducted in the private blockchain of the platform and can further be inspected by the community in case of any doubt or conflict. The scout continues his work with the players and submits periodical analytical reports considering their performance. Analysts review the reports and can vote for or against the contract renewal with the (a) talent and (b) Head of Scouting Network, who made the final proposal on signing the contract with talent.  For more details please have a look at the Infrastructure Layer section in the White Paper: https://tokenstars.com/upload/files/team_whitepaper.pdf

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Talent scouting module implements platform-based interactions between TokenStars, talent scouts (represented by professional part-time scouts, youth coaches or incentivized token holders) and TEAM token holders who have volunteered to become Analysts. The module is tightly integrated with the voting module.  Please have a look at the section Talent Scouting Module in the White Paper with the detailed procedure description: https://tokenstars.com/upload/files/team_whitepaper.pdf

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Brands seek for combination of transparent advertising formats, as well as for more engaged audiences.  TokenStars platform provides brands an opportunity to access highly involved fan audience and increase the efficiency of campaigns by implementing advertising smart contracts.  1. Each celebrity has a clear profile with detailed information on their followers and marketing metrics ‚Äì insights on followers, available stats and data on previous partnerships with advertisers. Platform transparency allows advertisers to choose most 'suitable' celebrity to work with. Both successful PROs and rising celebrities can be involved in partnership.  2. To ensure even higher engagement and interest towards the product, the platform allows advertisers to merge the celebrity campaign with e-commerce module. That means advertisers can cooperate with celebrities and create online-stores within the platform with advertised goods and services. Online stores increase product awareness and revenue.  3. TokenStars platform will develop own technical assets to provide efficient advertising options. ÔÇ∑ own Data Management Platform (DMP) to collect and analyze information on audience to provide more precise targeting options. ÔÇ∑ 3rd party ad server will allow run ads across the platform. ÔÇ∑ using exclusive audience data and industry-standard media buying solutions (DSP) will give an opportunity to programmatic advertising campaigns.  4. Smart Contract allows to track campaign efficiency (information on traffic, user engagement, user insights) and pass stats to advertisers' side via in-house-developed ad tech solution.  5. Smart Contract provides lower partnership costs due to absence of intermediators and ensures clear pricing policy. All advertisers will know the final price and list of services to be delivered

Author: zaphold
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: That's a bit of a pickle, isn't it? On the one hand, it's clear that Next-Level's unwillingness to pass KYC is nothing but an attempt to make more money, as ETH and BTC have by now about quadrupled in price. On the other hand, TokenStars representatives here did claim that they would refund anyone who doesn't want to pass KYC. I guess what they didn't anticipate, however, I take it mostly because of their utter commitment to the project and belief in its future success is how many people would want to get out of the project now if given the opportunity. Because let's face it, most of the participants went in in the hopes of future gains above all else.  TokenStars have been very honest right from the get-go, never ducking or dodging a comment and always responding in a timely fashion, and I would hate to see someone taking advantage of that. Next-Level and the likes should be left to live with their prior decision to commit, and if they don't want to pass KYC it's their own deal, no refunds should follow. After all, they did sign the agreement and it was all there in black and white.  TokenStars should feel no guilt either for not being willing to refund because of that one comment that they made. They could've just said no refunds period, and would've been right to do so. Instead they decided to be too kind for their own good and make sure that those who failed to give the agreement a proper read wouldn't get screwed. And now people try to screw them for that. No way!

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: KYC procedure was stated in the Agreement of sales from the very beginning with which you agreed before sending crypto to us.  We ask to pass the KYC because this is the user's obligation under the agreement of sale of tokens;  The refund is our right and not an obligation. The return of money will be only to those whom we ourselves consider restricted and assign this status.  If you refuse or give fake documents - you don't become restricted, and, accordingly, don't receive the refund.  Please upload the documents to your dashboard.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: We planned to start different verticals and different tokens from the very beginning. Our vision is to become a full-cycle talent management agency with decentralized talent scouting and decentralized talent promotion processes.    Over the course of August, September and October, we‚Äôve personally met or had phone calls with several Olympic champions, world champions, coaches and agents. We‚Äôre incredibly grateful for all the advice we‚Äôve received. On multiple occasions, we‚Äôve heard the question ‚ÄòWhy do you separate different kinds of sport into different verticals and use different tokens?‚Äô Both approaches are viable and have their PROs and CONs.    We‚Äôve considered all arguments and decided to go with the 1 TEAM token.  So there will be 2 tokens. ACE for tennis and TEAM is for other sports and entertainment (football, hockey, poker, Hollywood).

Author: shinzai
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hi, Congratulations on the successful ACE token sale!  I have a few questions regarding the TEAM token sale & eventual conversion from ACE:  1) Is there a last date to submit the ACE KYC? 2) Is there a last date to convert ACE to TEAM? 3) What will happend if I don't decide within that time limit? 4) When and where can I find the whitepaper for the TEAM token sale? 5a) Why do you offer ACE token holders the choice to convert ACE tokens to TEAM (with 40% bonus)? Would it not make more sense to just hold a separate token sale for TEAM (as you already are). I feel all this does is creating uncertainty regarding the number of ACE tokens & token holders. 5b) What if everyone but me for example decide to convert their ACE to TEAM? I feel that might affect the ACE token value (understatement of the year). 5c) If you are confident in the future of the ACE token - why give the offer to convert to another token? Why not just let interested people join the TEAM token sale? That way no uncertainty regarding ACE is added. No downside. 6) If I convert ACE to TEAM, will my funds be taken from the ACE platform to the TEAM platform?  I also feel I would like more info about the TEAM token sale before I make my decision.  Cheers  Edit: added question 6.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hi. Thank you for your questions The most of the answers you could find in our Medium post (https://medium.com/@TokenStars/https-medium-com-tokenstars-join-the-team-10-news-from-tokenstars-98464eb711ed), but let us answer you here.  1) Yes, November 27th. 2) If you mean with 40% bonus - yes, November 27th. 3) You will stay with ACE tokens and won't get 40% bonus on conversion. 4) The TEAM whitepaper is not announced yet, please stay tuned for upcoming news. 5a) Long time ago we promised to provide ACE tokenholders with one-time 40% bonus for converting ACE into other verticals' tokens. So we keep the promises. 5b) As we can see from the activities, some people stay with ACE, some people convert ACE to TEAM, so you definitely won't be the only one Things are going well with ACE anyway. We receive more and more players‚Äô applications, we get better agency name recognition among the leading tennis players. The number one rule of the system administrator is not to touch something if it is working. Additionally, every token holder accepted the ACE token sale agreement and bought ACE token (a digital good, crypto access key). We can‚Äôt (and we won‚Äôt) replace one digital good with another one without community and ACE token holders‚Äô consent. Our promises matter. If a token holder wants to exchange ACE token into TEAM with 40% bonus, they are more than welcome to do so in the Dashboard before transferring ACE to ERC-20 wallets. 5c) See 5a. TEAM is just another token of TokenStars, it's not a competitor. As you can see in our White Paper, since the beginning we planned to launch new verticals (football, poker, cybersports, etc), so we are just following the initial plan. The only thing which we have changed is that we united all future verticals in one token TEAM. Why did we decide to do that, you can read in our Medium post: https://medium.com/@TokenStars/https-medium-com-tokenstars-join-the-team-10-news-from-tokenstars-98464eb711ed. And of course there will be also TEAM token sale as well. 6) Yes.  Please find more information about TEAM token here: https://tokenstars.com/en/team and follow us on Telegram to be the first who will see all updates.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Why do you think that KYC is a trick?  The ‚Äòknow your client‚Äô (KYC) procedure is required by the banks and exchanges.  As our token sale agreement did not allow for US citizens and other restricted persons to participate in the sale, the KYC procedure allows to verify citizenship and make sure the token holders comply with those rules.  And after KYC our company will be able to open bank accounts in trustworthy banks but not in shady organizations.  10 out of the 14 largest exchanges on the market do not allow to conduct any operations to withdraw funds without going through a KYC (at least, a passport). To increase the limits, they ask for additional verification. And only 1 of the 14 exchanges allows you to start and withdraw fiat without KYC (and only in Japan).

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Star ICO Module: tokenizing time The star conducts his personal ICO, gets upfront payment for various exclusive communications with the fans (locker-room tour, dinners, chats, merchandize). Some offers are sold at auctions. Offers like video chats have an unlimited number of participants. Celebrity time is a precious and limited resource. Which is a fundamental growth factor. ‚ÄòAn Olympic champion‚Äô presells 50 hours of his communications with the fans, who redeem tokens on 1 on 1 training with the star, VIP dinner, a video chat and other exclusive offers.  Star ICO Module: tokenizing income At a stage II after tokenizing time, TokenStars platform will help stars tokenize their income. A rising star might sign a binding agreement which grants certain percentage of future personal incomes in return for upfront payment. This will most likely make the token a security token. So, the proper registration and legal framework will need to be implemented before launching this module. ‚ÄòHollywood star‚Äô is penniless after the divorce and rehab. He tokenizes 20% of his future incomes in return for fans‚Äô support today. He makes a hit movie, pays out 20% in tokens.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Why do I have to go through the KYC procedure to get my tokens?

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: There are 2 reasons for that:  1. As our token sale agreement did not allow for US citizens and other restricted persons to participate in the sale, the KYC procedure allows to verify citizenship and make sure the token holders comply with those rules.  2. And after KYC our company will be able to open bank accounts in trustworthy banks but not in shady organizations.  The ‚Äòknow your client‚Äô procedure takes only 5 minutes and it is required by the banks and exchanges. As our token sale agreement did not allow for US citizens and other restricted persons to participate in the sale, the KYC procedure allows to verify citizenship and make sure the token holders comply with those rules.  All the files are stored confidentially on Amazon servers. You need to upload your passport (or other government issued ID) and a 2nd document, verifying your current place of residence. There is a detailed description of the process in your personal dashboard.  Once the documents are uploaded, we verify them, confirm (or ask for additional clarification) and approve the token issue to the ERC-20 wallets, you‚Äôll specify in the dashboard. As simple as that.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Join the TEAM: 10 News from TokenStars   Congratulations! We‚Äôre finally here. ACE token sale is coming to the end and we‚Äôd like to make several announcements and answer all the burning questions. When will I get my tokens? What about the exchanges? Next verticals? How can I convert ACE tokens?  1. How can I get my ACE tokens?  We‚Äôll be issuing tokens in weekly batches to everyone who successfully passes the KYC procedure. Starting on November 7th‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäNovember 14th‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäNovember 21st‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääand (if anyone‚Äôs left) November 28th.   2. What is KYC?  The ‚Äòknow your client‚Äô procedure takes only 5 minutes and it is required by the banks and exchanges. As our token sale agreement did not allow for US citizens and other restricted persons to participate in the sale, the KYC procedure allows to verify citizenship and make sure the token holders comply with those rules.  All the files are stored confidentially on Amazon servers. You need to upload your passport (or other government issued ID) and a 2nd document, verifying your current place of residence. There is a detailed description of the process in your personal dashboard.  Once the documents are uploaded, we verify them, confirm (or ask for additional clarification) and approve the token issue to the ERC-20 wallets, you‚Äôll specify in the dashboard. As simple as that.  3. ACE on exchanges  We‚Äôve started talking to several exchanges (two out of the top-10 exchanges by volume) and expect news in the next 3‚Äì4 weeks. Please stay patient. It is easy to get listed on some low-quality exchange with no liquidity and shady ruled, but we all don‚Äôt need this.  Subscribe to the Telegram group to be among the first to know.  4. Converting ACE token  As promised, ACE tokens might be converted in your Dashboard into other verticals‚Äô tokens with 40% one-time bonus. Conversion only works in 1 direction (ACE into TEAM only, not vice versa), and you can only convert all ACE tokens you have at once, between October 27th and November 27th. Conversion is only available BEFORE you transfer ACE tokens to your personal wallet.   5. Next verticals ‚Äî‚ÄäALL TOGETHER‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäTEAM token  Over the course of August, September and October, we‚Äôve personally met or had phone calls with several Olympic champions, world champions, coaches and agents. We‚Äôre incredibly grateful for all the advice we‚Äôve received. On multiple occasions we‚Äôve heard the question ‚ÄòWhy do you separate different kinds of sport into different verticals and use different tokens?‚Äô  Both approaches are viable and have their PROs and CONs.   We‚Äôve considered all arguments and decided to go with the 1 TEAM token.   6. Why is ACE not included into TEAM  Things are going well with the tennis vertical. We receive more and more players‚Äô applications, we get better agency name recognition among the leading tennis players. The number one rule of the system administrator is not to touch something if it is working.  Additionally, every token holder accepted the ACE token sale agreement and bought ACE token (a digital good, crypto access key). We can‚Äôt (and we won‚Äôt) replace one digital good with another one without community and ACE token holders‚Äô consent. Our promises matter.  If a token holder wants to exchange ACE token into TEAM with 40% bonus, they are more than welcome to do so in the Dashboard before transferring ACE to ERC-20 wallets.  7. How is ACE token sale going  There are still a couple days to go with the token sale, but we can announce the preliminary results.  As you remember, for security reasons every token buyer received an individual payment address (created by the CoinPayments POS processor). Token sale proceeds are currently consolidated into the cold storages with the following addresses:  https://blockchain.info/address/3F7gofQYuwundAqCHxiA5oPxT3iNUtR2Yx   https://blockchain.info/address/1AqxymppuXWGq2PV56MrrdAdG7K7LW66pd   https://etherchain.org/account/0x77021B55eF2606253f7F18475ef390b0c8C07797    In addition to that, we‚Äôve sold 90 BTC worth of ACE tokens via the ICOBox platform.  So, the final amount will equal funds collected in BTC + funds collected in ETH + funds sold via resellers‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäKYC (rejected transactions).  As of 11AM CET October, 30 the amount equals $4,928,107. The number will fluctuate, depending on the currency exchange rates.  8. What are your plans going forward with TEAM token  We are talking to dozens of football, poker, eSports and hockey players, managers and agents. The goal is to form an Advisory board of globally respected experts.  Our technology team is working on the web interfaces and smart contracts for the platform.  Our marketing team is in talks about local sports media partnerships (similar to Sports.ru model).  The closed pre-sale will start in about a week. The date of the token sale will be announced later in November.  9. What about the STAR token  We‚Äôre still keeping secret the details about the STAR token. We can only tell that it is designed for globally recognizable celebrities (movie stars, musicians whose name rings a bell from Tokyo to Paris) and that we‚Äôre in negotiations with a good number of such stars. Stay tuned!   10. Fun with flags  In the meantime, we are preparing some statistics about the token holders geographical distribution, average purchases and other interesting data.  Meet our big spenders‚Äî the highest average purchases were coming from China and Ukraine.   And here are our careful savers‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäNigeria and Brazil showed the lowest average purchases. Fun fact‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääthe average ACE token purchase in China was more than 20x higher than in Nigeria.   How about payment methods? Looks like a lot of BTC fans in Thailand, Ukraine, Hong Kong, China, and Switzerland‚Ä¶   Meanwhile, over 90% of payments in Nigeria, Indonesia, Malaysia, Morocco and India were made in ETH.   ACE token sale continues‚Ää‚Äî‚Äävisit our official website for more details.  Stay updated‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääfollow the project‚Äôs social media channels on: Facebook Twitter Telegram Medium LinkedIn Reddit or take a look at our video on YouTube.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars is the first platform to tokenize celebrities. It aims to disrupt the huge $50 billion talent management industry by decentralizing it and providing funding and promotion resources to rising stars.   Young (potential) celebrities need funding and provide share of their income in return. Already successful professionals need more advertising contracts in return for agency commission.  Starting with issuing ACE tokens for the tennis vertical, the company plans to expand into new verticals in 2017, including football (GOAL tokens), poker (CHIP), and cybersports.  ACE offers unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Old-fashioned scouting process should be replaced with a decentralized approach. We believe that the Global Scouting Network of 600 part-time analysts spread globally and properly motivated financially will be more efficient than the full-time 60 employees focused on making friends with local Tennis Federations‚Äô presidents.    With the help of ACE tutorials, the Scouts will: ‚Ä¢ Crunch data (local kids‚Äô and juniors‚Äô rankings, and local tournament results) and determine potential ‚Äòtargets‚Äô ‚Ä¢ Reach out to players, parents, coaches, and tennis club owners in local social networks ‚Ä¢ Submit applications via the ACE website to our full-time scouts ‚Ä¢ Hold assessment sessions at players‚Äô locations (no need for expensive 2-week travel to a global HQ, like IMG does) ‚Ä¢ Use the most modern connected equipment during assessments, for example, the Babolat smart racquet which gathers a variety of data during the game (serve speed, shots hit map, rally time, etc.) ‚Ä¢ Use a unique internal players‚Äô assessment checklist (50+ parameters ranging from the strictly technical side to the players‚Äô psycho-type or their parents‚Äô involvement). This will allow for development of a standardized process and legitimate player comparisons ‚Ä¢ Submit players‚Äô assessment reports to the ACE community for their professional assessment through DCV (Decentralized community voting) mechanism  Scouts will receive significant amounts of money for successful recommendations in order to be motivated (up to $10000+).  We don't sign only one player, we select cohorts of 20-30 players, which raises the chances of success. Please check out our three forecasts (pessimistic, realistic, and optimistic) on p.51 of the White paper. https://tokenstars.com/upload/files/ace_by_tokenstars_whitepaper.pdf

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: A contract will be signed with athletes aged between 13 and 14 who are likely to become famous in the future. There are a lot of people who have to leave sports while they might be your future star because of financial resource problems. These young players will have both financial resources and promotions for free.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: The funding problem of rising stars is usually solved by agencies. They sign 13- to 15-year-old tennis players, finance them, and sometimes even run academies (IMG bought the famous Nick Bollettieri Academy). After the player starts climbing the ATP or WTA rankings, the agencies help with advertising deals and take a 20% cut from the revenues (with priority rights to the first cover incurred costs).  We expect to sign the players at 13-14 years of age and to sign their first sponsorship deals at 14. Usually, these are relatively small, like $10-30K for every sponsor per player per year.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hello!  Here it is the use of ACE tokens: 1. Means to use and interact with the ACE platform. ACE are the product tokens, it carry backbone functions of the ACE platform. The full functionality of the ACE platform is available only for ACE token holders. We plan to place the ACE tokens on cryptographic token exchanges.  2. Form of expression of ACE community opinion. The ACE platform will provide ACE token holders with the  opportunity to express their opinion regarding the particular operational issues of the ACE agency‚Äôs business through the decentralized community voting (DCV) mechanism, which is in more detail described in section 7.1 of our White Paper. These decisions, expressed through DCV mechanism, will serve as the advisory guidelines for the ACE agency‚Äôs management. The agency‚Äôs management team and executives will consistently admit the results of ACE community voting to their consideration.  3. Form of settlement. The ACE tokens will be used as a form of settlement in the transactions conducted within the ACE platform. In particular, ACE tokens holders may be able to use their ACE tokens to purchase services and products to be offered within the ACE platform, as it specified in Section 7.2 of our White Paper.  4. Means to power ACE platform‚Äôs compensation system. The ACE platform builds well-balanced motivation  system that encourages its agents, specifically Scouts, Promoters and Advertisers, to perform their functions better  thereby increasing the effectiveness of the entire ACE ecosystem and its benefits to the ACE community. To be motivated to use the ACE platform further, its agents may receive compensation for their active participation in ACE ecosystem, as descried in Sections 6.2 and 6.3 of the White Paper. Compensation will be paid in the ACE tokens, that allows the agents to participate in the growth of ACE ecosystem.  You are more then welcome to see more in details in our White Paper (7. Use of Tokens).

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: The system of children's and youth schools is very outdated - professionals do not often come out from the schools. The individual academies now are effective. We plan to work not with children, but with athletes at the beginning of a career. Nowadays tennis players are left to themselves and work individually: they go to tournaments covering their own expense to buy tickets, hire coaches, rent courts.  Maria Sharapova's father even washed dishes in the USA to earn extra money to pay for his daughter's tennis. I believe you also heard about Jamie Vardi, how he worked at the plant and played in the lower divisions up to 22 years.  Young talents often drop out the sport due to lack of funding and lack of sponsors. Tokenstars can provide all of this. Traditional agencies sign just a few of young talents, while a lot of good athletes are not given proper attention. We want to improve the search process and give an opportunity for young sportsmen with the help of blockchain and decentralization.

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Thank you!  Not everybody gets to experience a real-life Cinderella story like Jamie Vardy and Myroslav Klose had. They were struggling to get attention from big teams while working a full-time job to support themselves and even their families, but in the end still became huge football stars.  Not many young players are so persistent and motivated as Klose and Vardy but they may have the same talent. Nevertheless, the only thing they need is support at the right time to achieve new goals. TokenStars definitely helps young players to break through to professional sport.

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: You can use ACE tokens in different ways.  ACE is a product token which offers unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc. These services are bought for tokens. The more often a token is used, the better it is for all participants.  Agency commissions will be converted into tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow. As a result, the agency commissions will grow. Accordingly, commissions will be converted into tokens, which means that tokens are supposed to be bought on the market. The more revenue, the more is supposed to be bought. This positively impacts the internal economy.  The ACE token plays a crucial role in the ACE ecosystem, since it provides voting rights in the decentralized community voting mechanism. ACE holders will have the opportunity to vote on various decisions, thus influencing the success of the platform. Then, it serves as a fundamental unit of accounting and a method of payment for its agents, specifically scouts, promoters, and advertisers.

Author: shinzai
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Hi! I have an issue with the short term value.  As far as I understand you raised 377 btc during pre-sale and 828 btc so far during main sale.  The pre-sale was made in cooperation with IcoBox, in which participants could use icobox tokens to buy your tokens at 75% discount, correct? I conclude that must mean that at this moment in time about 64% (377*4/(377*4+828) = 0.64) of the tokens has been bought at 75% discount, correct?  Won't that put a strain on the token value when tokens are released on the market? People might just sell at lower than ico price since they still make a nice profit.  I admit I haven't looked into the ico very much. It does interest me, but this above issue prevents me from investing atm.  Comments? Maybe I have misunderstood something

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: Thank you for your interest and such a deep analysis!  You are right about our cooperation with ICObox, particularly we participated in ICOS, campaign for token swap.  In scope of ICOS you receive 75% discount if you invested via ICOBOX. However, there was only 96 hour period from the time it shows up on the site to the time it closes, and the amount of ACE tokens available for swap was limited too. Even though ACE token swap program was oversubscribed, that doesn't mean that all raised 377 btc during pre-sale were bought with the 75% discount   The exact amount of tokens which were distributed via ICOS will be published separately.  Regarding the issue how do we see the token price grow, first of all, ACE is a product token which offers unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc. These services are bought for tokens. The more often a token is used, the better it is for all participants.  Second, agency commissions will be paid in tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow. As a result, the agency commissions will grow. Accordingly, sponsors will convert our commissions into tokens, which means buying tokens on the market. The more revenue, the more we buy. This positively impacts the internal economy.  You are more than welcome with more questions if you have any! And thank you again for rising up such an interesting question!

Body: How do we and the project make our money back as investors?  Do we get a % of future earnings?

Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars‚Äô business model is based on the traditional talent management agency model. We receive a 20-30% commission from the players‚Äô sponsorship contracts and net prize money. This revenue will be converted into tokens.  You don't get a fixed percentage of the future earnings because ACE token is a product token but you can benefit from the project in different ways. For example, you can become a scout or a promoter and receive payment for successful recommendations of a promising junior or for promoting our signed athletes.  Besides, ACE token offers unmatched opportunities, like hours of training with players, meetings, tickets, advertising with celebrities for platform users, etc. These services are bought for tokens. The more often a token is used, the better it is for all participants.  And don't forget that agency commissions will be paid in tokens. As TokenStars develops, the number of sponsorship contracts signed by the players will grow. As a result, the agency commissions will grow. Accordingly, sponsors will convert our commissions into tokens, which means buying tokens on the market. The more revenue, the more will be bought from the market. This positively impacts the internal economy.   What do you think about this concept?

Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: üéæ Meet Design Advisor of TokenStars Mikhailius Derkach üéæ  Development and promotion of TokenStars brand by our potential athletes is very important for our success. This is what our Design advisor Mikhailius Derkach is responsible for.  Mikhailius is the Founder of ProExpedition Adventures‚Äô Journal,  designer, and usability specialist. He took part in many digital projects, awarded by few marketing and advertising festivals. He participated in the creation of advertising campaigns for such brands as Google, Samsung, McDonald's, Lego, P&G, Coca-Cola.  Also, Mikhailius is Ex Art-Director of Leo Burnett Moscow, Member of Art Directors Club Russia. Author: TokenStars
Title: [ANN][ICO] TokenStars: Tokenize Celebrities
Body: TokenStars ACE ICO Starts on August 31, 2017  Dear TokenStars supporters and potential ACE contributors,  Due to ongoing DDoS attacks on our website that have been taking place for the last few days, we have decided to delay the TokenStars ACE token crowdsale previously scheduled for August 24, 2017. But‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääonly for 7 days.  The new ICO start date is August 31, 2017.  That extra week will allow our technology team and our security partners from Wallarm to significantly strengthen the safety of TokenStars‚Äô online assets, improve the anti-hacker approaches and the tools that we already use, as well as to investigate and implement additional mechanisms to guarantee the maximum level of security during the entire ICO period.  Being a certified expert in Information Systems and Telecommunications Security, TokenStars‚Äô CTO Andrey Toukmanov is sure that all our systems will be put under the ultimate control and provided with immunity against attacks by August 31. To shed more light on what we are doing, here are the key points on our way to the uttermost stability and resistibility:  We conduct the anti-DDoS monitoring and protection with the help of our partners at Wallarm.  We moved our hosting to Heroku, this provider has multiple security features out of the box that we are tuning up right now.  We will arrange an additional audit of the smart contract and website code, most probably with New Alchemy.  To sum up: We know about the attacks. We are doing our best to keep everything under our control‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääand these efforts are successful, you can see it because our website is working normally. We are delaying the start of the TokenStars ACE token crowdsale until August 31, 2017, in order to protect our respected supporters and potential contributors against any security challenges that might show up. We know how to deal with all current issues in due time.  Thank you for being with us. Stay tuned. Ask your questions, please, if any.

Having successfully started with the ACE token sale for tennis ($4.9M+ raised as of the sale end!), TokenStars has enhanced its team with top-notch experts and stars to launch the TEAM token:  Lothar Matth√§us, Valery Karpin (football), Tommy Haas, Robin S√∂derling, Cedric Pioline, Anastasia Myskina (tennis), Nikita Kucherov (hockey), Alexander Anter (poker) and Rico Torres (Hollywood) are among the famous celebrities supporting TokenStars!        Designed as a toolkit, the TokenStars platform consists of 12 integrated modules grouped in 4 layers by function:  1) crowdfunding, enabling prospective talents to raise funds;  2) infrastructure, providing the community with tools for key activities (scouting, voting, betting);  3) fan community, allowing celebrities to grow their social capital and offering fans higher involvement;  4) advertising, delivering smart and transparent data as well as engaged audiences to brands for more efficient promotion campaigns.      ‚öôÔ∏è Contests & Charity Module ‚öôÔ∏è, the first part of the TokenStars platform, is out!  Give it a real try now! Join our blockchain-based üéÑ Charity Crypto Xmas Auction üéÑ and get exclusive stuff from celebrities!      As a utility token, TEAM will be used in most of the interaction activities powered by the TokenStars platform, including repayment of agency commissions from advertisers and supported talents, providing incentives to fans and external agents for finding promising talents (scouts) and for promoting celebrities (promoters), making betting bids, participating in the voting polls, getting access to exclusive offers from celebrities, and so on.      TokenStars develops its platform on the blockchain to make it transparent and verifiable, create a powerful global community, ensure lower money transfer costs and faster transactions with no need in a third party, as well as to eliminate middlemen in and bring more transparency to the celebrity management industry.      Worldwide famous stars support TokenStars as its Ambassadors:      Based on a proven business model, TokenStars is lead by an experienced team with background at Groupon, Leo Burnett, Evernote, Rambler&Co and Mail.Ru Group. Each item is unique and will be sold to the donor who places the highest bid (accepted in BTC, ETH and TokenStars ACE tokens).
